	<p>
		Aalto Global Impact ran its second ACCESS workshop this year in Cape Town on 8 November 2012 during the “World Design Capital: Helsinki Meets Cape Town” event. Organised in collaboration with Cape Peninsula University of Technology (CPUT), Cape Town Partnership (CTP) and Cape Town Design Network (CTDN), the Aalto Global Impact ACCESS workshop brought together some 80 participants from Finland and South Africa, and activated about 12 students/volunteers from CPUT and Aalto University in the coordination of the event. <br><br>Everyone had a voice! Each participant had a chance to post his/her burning issue around the main drivers of the WDC Cape Town bid book: infrastructural development, social cohesion, knowledge economy and other (as an open category for unforeseen thematic).<br><br>Reorganised into smaller discussion groups, the open format of the event initiated dialogue for new ideas and some concrete projects around the WDC Cape Town themes of “Live Design, Transform Lives - reconnecting, rebuilding and repositioning the city through the transformative power of design”. <br>You may revisit the ACCESS event, its outputs and the people participating with the help of the following documentation:<br><br><ul><li>a comprehensive presentation of the event, showing its process, its participants and what the groups have worked on: http://dl.dropbox.com/u/86104439/HKImeetsCT_nov12/ACCESS_design%20needs%20your%20voice.pdf</li><li>a selection of photos: https://www.dropbox.com/sh/8k368mvye3engix/XhGKr3uXxj</li><li>a blog post from a Creative Sustainability student's perspective: </li><li>https://blogs.aalto.fi/insouthafrica/2012/11/14/3-0-%E2%80%93-access-event-%E2%80%9Cdesign-needs-your-voice%E2%80%9D-and-pecha-kuchas-at-reception/ </li><li>Cape Town Partnership: http://www.capetownpartnership.co.za/</li><li>Cape Peninsula University of Technology: http://sharpenyourmind.co.za/departments</li><li>Cape Town Design Network: http://www.ctdn.co.za/</li></ul><p>https://www.y